WEBVTT

00:01.262 --> 00:03.003
PREVIOUSLY ON "THE 100"...

00:03.046 --> 00:04.482
DIYOZA: THE VALLEY IS OURS.

00:04.526 --> 00:06.919
AS LONG AS YOU STAY HERE,
WE WON'T HAVE A PROBLEM.

00:06.963 --> 00:09.009
OCTAVIA: THE HYDROFARM
IS BARELY FEEDING US NOW,

00:09.052 --> 00:12.055
SO IF THIS IS THE LAST
LIVING VALLEY ON EARTH,

00:12.099 --> 00:13.361
THEN IT SHOULD BE OURS.

00:13.404 --> 00:16.016
BELLAMY: DIYOZA
THINKS THE SAME THING.

00:16.059 --> 00:17.278
AND SO WE FIGHT.

00:17.321 --> 00:20.063
OH, MY GOD,
THEY'RE BREEDING THEM.

00:20.107 --> 00:21.282
[GASPING]

00:21.325 --> 00:22.761
YOU'RE GONNA
SUCK TODAY.

00:22.805 --> 00:25.112
NO ONE CAN THINK THAT
YOU'D MAKE A GOOD COMMANDER.

00:25.155 --> 00:27.418
-YAAH! UH!
-YAAH!

00:27.462 --> 00:30.987
OCTAVIA: MADI, I COULD
REALLY USE A SECOND.

00:31.031 --> 00:32.249
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

00:32.293 --> 00:33.859
CLARKE: I HAVE A QUESTION
FOR COLONEL DIYOZA.

00:33.903 --> 00:35.731
WHAT WOULD IT TAKE FOR YOU
TO SHARE THE VALLEY?

00:35.774 --> 00:38.081
DIYOZA: SHORT OF
AN UNCONDITIONAL SURRENDER,

00:38.125 --> 00:39.169
NOTHING.

00:39.213 --> 00:40.431
OCTAVIA WILL
NEVER SURRENDER.

00:40.475 --> 00:43.043
THAT'S WHY WE'RE
GONNA TAKE HER OUT.

00:45.828 --> 00:48.483
DIYOZA, ON RADIO: I DON'T CARE
HOW YOU MAKE IT HAPPEN, CLARKE.

00:48.526 --> 00:50.615
KILL OCTAVIA IS YOU HAVE TO.

00:50.659 --> 00:53.183
BRING HER TO ME IN CHAINS,
AND I'LL DO IT FOR YOU,

00:53.227 --> 00:55.533
OR SHE CAN
SURRENDER HERSELF,

00:55.577 --> 00:59.233
BUT YOUR RED QUEEN
DOESN'T SEEM LIKE THE TYPE.

00:59.276 --> 01:02.410
LET US WORRY
ABOUT THAT.

01:02.453 --> 01:05.108
DIYOZA: WE HAVE
AN UNDERSTANDING, THEN.

01:05.152 --> 01:08.329
-WE DO.
-GOOD.

01:08.372 --> 01:09.895
DIYOZA: CALL ME BACK
WHEN IT'S DONE,

01:09.939 --> 01:13.073
AND WE CAN WORK OUT
THE DETAILS OF YOUR CROSSING.

01:13.116 --> 01:14.117
OVER AND OUT.

01:14.161 --> 01:15.553
-NO WAY.
-BELLAMY--

01:15.597 --> 01:18.252
WE ARE NOT KILLING
MY SISTER, CLARKE.

01:18.295 --> 01:20.645
I DON'T CARE
HOW CRAZY SHE IS.

01:20.689 --> 01:23.083
RUN THE LOOP.
THE ROVER'S CHARGED.

01:23.126 --> 01:25.041
WE'RE GETTING
OUR FRIENDS.

01:25.085 --> 01:29.915
THAT WAS RECKLESS.
WE HAD A PLAN. YOU AGREED.

01:29.959 --> 01:35.095
CLARKE: THAT WAS BEFORE OCTAVIA
MADE MADI HER SECOND.

01:35.138 --> 01:36.400
THAT ARMY MARCHES TO WAR

01:36.444 --> 01:39.099
AS SOON AS THEY FIND OUT
THE EYE IS DOWN.

01:39.142 --> 01:40.491
I CAN'T LET THAT HAPPEN.

01:40.535 --> 01:42.319
HARPER: SO WE
DON'T TELL ANYONE?

01:42.363 --> 01:43.929
MONTY: THEY'LL KNOW
AS SOON AS WE DRIVE AWAY.

01:43.973 --> 01:45.322
BELLAMY: OH, WHO CARES?
WE GRAB MADI, AND WE GO.

01:45.366 --> 01:46.715
BELLAMY, SHE'S
BY HER SIDE.

01:46.758 --> 01:50.153
-SHE'S MY SISTER, CLARKE.
-I KNOW.

01:50.197 --> 01:51.372
TELL ME WHAT ELSE TO DO.

01:51.415 --> 01:55.115
-WE STOP THE WAR.
-HOW?

01:55.158 --> 01:56.638
-ALGAE.
-MONTY--

01:56.681 --> 01:58.161
MONTY: COOPER ALREADY
GAVE ME PERMISSION

01:58.205 --> 01:59.771
TO SHOW
WHAT IT CAN DO.

01:59.815 --> 02:01.251
SHE'S MEETING ME BEFORE
THE AFTERNOON MEAL

02:01.295 --> 02:02.818
SO I CAN
TAKE HER TO THE--

02:02.861 --> 02:04.776
-THAT'S ENOUGH.
-HEY, GIVE IT BACK.

02:04.820 --> 02:06.213
HARPER: MONTY, BELLAMY'S RIGHT.
COOPER'S WORSE THAN OCTAVIA.

02:06.256 --> 02:08.432
NO OFFENSE.

02:08.476 --> 02:11.218
BESIDES, THE FIRST BATCH
PUT MURPHY IN A COMA

02:11.261 --> 02:12.697
FOR ALMOST A WEEK.

02:12.741 --> 02:14.308
BY THE TIME
IT'S READY TO EAT--

02:14.351 --> 02:15.744
MONTY:
THE FIRST CULTURE,

02:15.787 --> 02:17.311
AND WE'RE NOT
GONNA EAT IT THIS TIME.

02:17.354 --> 02:19.182
WE'RE GONNA FEED IT
TO THE PLANTS.

02:19.226 --> 02:20.444
IF I CAN MAKE THE FARM
VIABLE AGAIN,

02:20.488 --> 02:22.577
THEN WE'LL STILL
HAVE A CHANCE.

02:25.319 --> 02:27.712
OCTAVIA:
THE SPY DID HER JOB?

02:27.756 --> 02:31.238
UH, WE WERE JUST
ABOUT TO SEND FOR YOU.

02:31.281 --> 02:34.197
TOLD YOU ECHO
WOULD GET IT DONE.

02:34.241 --> 02:36.243
CAN THE ENEMY
STILL SEE US?

02:36.286 --> 02:38.810
FOR NOW, YES.
IT'S TECHNICAL, BUT--

02:38.854 --> 02:42.466
HE HAS TO RUN A LOOP
TO MASK OUR TROOP MOVEMENTS.

02:42.510 --> 02:44.425
WHEN THE TIME COMES,
WE NEED TO CLEAR THE SURFACE

02:44.468 --> 02:46.209
TO REDUCE THE RISK
OF ANYONE NOTICING

02:46.253 --> 02:48.211
THE SAME PEOPLE MOVING
IN THE SAME DIRECTION

02:48.255 --> 02:51.040
AGAIN AND AGAIN.

02:51.083 --> 02:55.653
WELL DONE,
MONTY.

02:55.697 --> 02:59.440
LOAD THE WORMS
INTO THE ROVER

02:59.483 --> 03:04.009
AND MOBILIZE THE ARMY.

03:04.053 --> 03:05.707
WAR IS HERE.

03:48.358 --> 03:51.666
[DOOR OPENS]

03:51.709 --> 03:53.363
HE'S ALL YOURS,
COLONEL.

03:53.407 --> 03:55.496
DIYOZA: THANK YOU, ROBERT.

03:55.539 --> 03:57.759
GOING SOMEWHERE,
KANE?

03:57.802 --> 04:00.022
DO I NEED PERMISSION
FOR THAT?

04:00.065 --> 04:02.459
-YES.
-OK.

04:02.503 --> 04:04.331
I WAS GOING TO
THE SOUTHWEST QUADRANT

04:04.374 --> 04:06.289
TO MAP OUT
A SETTLEMENT.

04:06.333 --> 04:07.595
[COUGHING]

04:07.638 --> 04:12.252
JUST BREATHE, ROBERT.
IT'S OK.

04:12.295 --> 04:14.297
COMES AND GOES.
I'LL BE FINE.

04:14.341 --> 04:15.820
DAMN RIGHT YOU WILL.

04:15.864 --> 04:17.692
NEW DOC'S WORKING
ON A CURE.

04:17.735 --> 04:20.912
WHY NOT GIVE HIM
SOMETHING FOR THE PAIN?

04:20.956 --> 04:24.176
DIYOZA: MEANWHILE,
WHY DON'T YOU GET OFF YOUR FEET?

04:24.220 --> 04:26.309
YOU LOOK LIKE HELL.

04:26.353 --> 04:29.312
THANK YOU,
COLONEL.

04:29.356 --> 04:33.577
[ROBERT COUGHING]

04:37.668 --> 04:39.409
LIST OF THE PEOPLE
YOU KILLED?

04:39.453 --> 04:42.456
FOR THAT, I NEED
A BIGGER NOTEBOOK.

04:42.499 --> 04:44.414
WHY AM I HERE,
COLONEL?

04:44.458 --> 04:47.548
I GOT AN INTERESTING
CALL ON THE RADIO--

04:47.591 --> 04:49.158
ABBY'S DAUGHTER.

04:49.201 --> 04:51.595
CLARKE RADIOED? WHY?

04:51.639 --> 04:55.164
I THINK SHE MAY TRY
AND KILL YOUR RED QUEEN.

04:55.207 --> 04:56.731
SHE'LL GET KILLED.

04:56.774 --> 05:00.038
MAYBE, BUT I TOLD HER
ONCE IT'S DONE

05:00.082 --> 05:01.518
AND WONKRU
SURRENDERS...

05:01.562 --> 05:02.519
[RADIO STATIC]

05:02.563 --> 05:04.565
WE'LL SHARE
THIS VALLEY.

05:04.608 --> 05:07.437
MURPHY: TESTING, TESTING
FOR THE 200TH TIME.

05:07.481 --> 05:09.309
THIS IS JOHN MURPHY.

05:09.352 --> 05:11.572
THAT'S JOHN MURPHY.

05:11.615 --> 05:15.750
-LET ME TALK TO HIM.
-JUST WAIT.

05:15.793 --> 05:17.447
MURPHY: TESTING, TESTING.

05:17.491 --> 05:19.536
THIS IS JOHN MURPHY LOOKING
FOR COLONEL DIYOZA.

05:19.580 --> 05:23.235
DO YOU READ ME?

05:24.541 --> 05:26.935
WELL, IT'S SAFE TO SAY
YOU'RE BETTER

05:26.978 --> 05:29.503
AT BLOWING THINGS UP
THAN FIXING THEM.

05:29.546 --> 05:31.722
[EMORI SCOFFS]

05:31.766 --> 05:33.420
DIYOZA, ON RADIO:
THIS IS COLONEL DIYOZA.

05:33.463 --> 05:35.465
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

05:35.509 --> 05:41.341
BE STRONG, DIRECT,
UNRELENTING.

05:41.384 --> 05:43.038
WE HAVE MCCREARY.

05:43.081 --> 05:46.476
YOU EVER WANT TO SEE HIM ALIVE
AGAIN, YOU GIVE US RAVEN REYES.

05:49.131 --> 05:53.396
YOU KNOW HIM.
WILL HE FOLLOW THROUGH?

05:53.440 --> 05:55.398
PROBABLY.

05:55.442 --> 05:58.096
COLONEL, IF YOU
DON'T MAKE THE TRADE,

05:58.140 --> 06:03.145
-MCCREARY'S PEOPLE--
-BECOME MY PEOPLE.

06:03.188 --> 06:05.495
DIYOZA: YOU SHOULD HAVE LEARNED
THE LAST TIME

06:05.539 --> 06:07.497
YOU HELD MY PEOPLE HOSTAGE

06:07.541 --> 06:10.370
THAT I DON'T NEGOTIATE
WITH TERRORISTS.

06:10.413 --> 06:13.416
THAT'S FUNNY
COMING FROM YOU.

06:13.460 --> 06:16.680
LAST CHANCE,
OUR HOSTAGE FOR YOURS.

06:18.682 --> 06:22.077
DIYOZA: MAY GOD
HAVE MERCY ON HIS SOUL.

06:23.470 --> 06:26.037
[EXHALES]

06:26.081 --> 06:29.606
TWO RADIO CALLS,
TWO PROBLEMS SOLVED.

06:29.650 --> 06:33.523
WHAT ARE THE ODDS?

06:33.567 --> 06:36.134
THAT COULD'VE
GONE BETTER.

06:36.178 --> 06:39.442
CALL ME WHEN HE'S AWAKE.
I NEED SOME AIR.

06:39.486 --> 06:41.401
[MCCREARY WHEEZING]

06:42.532 --> 06:43.620
DIYOZA: COME ON, KANE.

06:43.664 --> 06:45.535
WITHOUT
GRAVEYARD MCCREARY,

06:45.579 --> 06:49.060
MY INTERNAL PROBLEM
IS SOLVED.

06:49.104 --> 06:52.934
WITHOUT THE RED QUEEN,
OUR PROBLEM EXTERNAL IS.

06:52.977 --> 06:54.675
THIS IS HOW
WE GET TO PEACE.

06:54.718 --> 06:58.156
IS IT? BECAUSE
FROM WHERE I'M STANDING,

06:58.200 --> 07:02.813
IT LOOKS LIKE WE'RE TRADING
ONE DICTATOR FOR ANOTHER--

07:02.857 --> 07:06.338
POLITICAL ASSASSINATIONS,
TORTURE,

07:06.382 --> 07:08.036
WRONGFUL IMPRISONMENT.

07:08.079 --> 07:09.951
THIS IS ABOUT ME
GIVING ABBY PILLS.

07:09.994 --> 07:11.692
YOU MEAN, FEEDING
AN ADDICT'S ADDICTION

07:11.735 --> 07:13.171
TO SAVE YOUR
PEOPLE'S LIVES

07:13.215 --> 07:16.174
WITHOUT A THOUGHT FOR
THE LIFE YOU'RE DESTROYING?

07:16.218 --> 07:17.524
YES. IT IS.

07:17.567 --> 07:19.569
I'VE SEEN THE HORRORS
WE INFLICT ON EACH OTHER

07:19.613 --> 07:21.919
IN THE NAME OF
SURVIVAL, COLONEL.

07:21.963 --> 07:26.794
GOD KNOWS I'M
AS GUILTY AS ANYONE,

07:26.837 --> 07:30.188
BUT WE'RE
ON THE BRINK HERE,

07:30.232 --> 07:32.277
ON THE EDGE OF AN ABYSS
I'VE STARED INTO BEFORE,

07:32.321 --> 07:35.585
AND I CAN TELL YOU,
HAVING SACRIFICED THE FEW

07:35.629 --> 07:39.676
TO SAVE THE MANY MORE TIMES
THAN I CARE TO ADMIT,

07:39.720 --> 07:43.941
EVENTUALLY, THE FEW
BECOMES THE MANY.

07:43.985 --> 07:46.074
THE ENDS DON'T ALWAYS
JUSTIFY THE MEANS,

07:46.117 --> 07:48.555
AND IF YOU DON'T
KNOW THAT BY NOW

07:48.598 --> 07:50.992
AFTER EVERYTHING
YOU'VE BEEN THROUGH...

07:55.344 --> 07:58.303
THEN YOU'RE JUST
AS BAD AS OCTAVIA...

07:59.522 --> 08:02.351
AND WE'RE
ALREADY LOST.

08:07.225 --> 08:09.489
[WHIRRING]

08:17.932 --> 08:21.283
THAT'S A FAIR AMOUNT
OF ABSCESSES, ISN'T IT, DOCTOR?

08:21.326 --> 08:23.764
[HEARTBEAT]

08:27.071 --> 08:29.552
ABBY: WAIT.
DID YOU FEEL THAT?

08:29.596 --> 08:31.902
FEEL WHAT?

08:31.946 --> 08:34.557
ONE OF THE ABSCESSES
BROKE APART.

08:34.601 --> 08:39.780
IT WAS THE SOUND WAVES.
I'M SURE OF IT.

08:39.823 --> 08:41.651
I CAN DISSOLVE THEM

08:41.695 --> 08:44.567
AND THEN SUCTION OUT
THE RESIDUE.

08:44.611 --> 08:48.092
HUH. I JUST NEED
MORE POWER.

08:54.751 --> 08:55.709
VINSON, WHERE
ARE YOU GOING?

08:55.752 --> 08:59.060
INSPIRATION
LOVES COMPANY.

09:01.889 --> 09:03.717
I'LL TAKE THAT
IF YOU DON'T MIND.

09:03.760 --> 09:06.284
HEY, MAN.

09:12.639 --> 09:14.292
A SONIC DRILL.

09:14.336 --> 09:17.905
IT USES SOUND WAVES
TO PULVERIZE ROCK.

09:17.948 --> 09:20.821
THAT'S A GOOD
IDEA, VINSON,

09:20.864 --> 09:22.823
BUT UNLESS THERE'S
A PRISONER AT THIS CAMP

09:22.866 --> 09:25.826
THAT'S AN ENGINEER,
THERE'S--

09:27.262 --> 09:28.393
[ZAP]

09:28.437 --> 09:29.612
SHAW: YAAGH! PLEASE--

09:29.656 --> 09:30.613
MAN: TURN IT UP
A LITTLE BIT.

09:30.657 --> 09:31.788
[ZAP]

09:31.832 --> 09:33.834
EEGH! UGH! UH!

09:33.877 --> 09:35.226
[PANTING]

09:35.270 --> 09:38.708
RAVEN, NO.
IT'S NOT YOUR FIGHT.

09:38.752 --> 09:40.318
IT'S OUR FAULT
HE'S HERE.

09:40.362 --> 09:42.582
I KNOW YOU'RE ANGRY,
BUT YOU SAID YOURSELF

09:42.625 --> 09:43.800
THEY CAN'T KILL HIM.

09:43.844 --> 09:47.761
HE'S THE ONLY
PERSON WHO--

09:47.804 --> 09:50.633
WE HAVE TO KILL HIM.

09:50.677 --> 09:52.069
NO WAY.

09:52.113 --> 09:54.724
RAVEN, THAT SHIP IS THEIR
BIGGEST STRATEGIC ADVANTAGE.

09:54.768 --> 09:57.248
WITHOUT
A PILOT TO FLY--

09:57.292 --> 10:00.556
I SAID NO.

10:12.394 --> 10:13.743
LISTEN TO ME.

10:13.787 --> 10:15.136
THERE'S NOTHING YOU HAVE
TO SAY THAT I COULD POSSIBLY--

10:15.179 --> 10:17.704
MY FRIEND ECHO
WANTS TO KILL YOU

10:17.747 --> 10:19.967
SO THEY HAVE NO ONE
TO FLY THE SHIP.

10:20.010 --> 10:23.971
IF YOU TELL DIYOZA,
I'LL DENY IT.

10:37.811 --> 10:39.639
[DOOR OPENS]

10:39.682 --> 10:41.118
INDRA: WE'RE READYING FOR WAR.

10:41.162 --> 10:43.033
DO YOU KNOW THE RISK I'M TAKING
MEETING YOU HERE?

10:43.077 --> 10:44.818
YES. THANK YOU
FOR COMING.

10:44.861 --> 10:45.906
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

10:45.949 --> 10:47.821
I TALKED
TO COLONEL DIYOZA.

10:47.864 --> 10:49.866
SHE'S OFFERING
ALL OF WONKRU

10:49.910 --> 10:51.738
SAFE PASSAGE
TO THE VALLEY.

10:51.781 --> 10:53.783
ALL OCTAVIA HAS TO DO
IS SURRENDER.

10:53.827 --> 10:55.611
AS IT'S BY NOW
YOU'VE REALIZED

10:55.655 --> 10:57.700
SHE WOULD NEVER DO THAT,
I'LL ASK YOU AGAIN.

10:57.744 --> 10:58.919
WHAT DO YOU
WANT FROM ME?

10:58.962 --> 11:00.311
BELLAMY: PEACE WITHOUT
WAR IS STILL POSSIBLE.

11:00.355 --> 11:02.705
NOW, YOU'RE HER ADVISOR.
SHE'LL LISTEN TO YOU.

11:02.749 --> 11:03.924
WHY WOULD I ADVISE
HER TO SURRENDER

11:03.967 --> 11:06.187
IN A WAR SHE'S
LIKELY TO WIN?

11:06.230 --> 11:07.884
THANKS TO YOU, WE
CAN MARCH FREELY

11:07.928 --> 11:09.756
ON THE ENEMY WHILE THE WORMS
RAVAGE THEM.

11:09.799 --> 11:11.496
BY THE TIME
WE GET TO THE VALLEY,

11:11.540 --> 11:13.890
THE ONLY THING LEFT TO DO
WILL BE TO CLEAN UP THE MESS.

11:13.934 --> 11:15.849
AND IF THE WORMS
RAVAGE THE VALLEY?

11:15.892 --> 11:18.721
A RISK SHE'S
WILLING TO TAKE.

11:18.765 --> 11:22.725
-ARE YOU?
-IT'S NOT UP TO ME.

11:22.769 --> 11:24.901
-WHAT IF IT WAS?
-CLARKE--

11:24.945 --> 11:27.469
INDRA: I WILL NOT HELP YOU
KILL MY LEADER.

11:27.512 --> 11:28.731
NEITHER WILL I.

11:28.775 --> 11:29.950
WHAT IF THE OUTCOME OF
THE WAR WASN'T CERTAIN,

11:29.993 --> 11:31.734
IF SHE DIDN'T
HAVE THE WORMS?

11:31.778 --> 11:32.735
WOULD SHE
STILL FIGHT?

11:32.779 --> 11:34.389
IF SHE DIDN'T
HAVE THE WORMS,

11:34.432 --> 11:36.652
BOTH SIDES WOULD TAKE
HEAVY LOSSES.

11:36.696 --> 11:37.958
EXACTLY.

11:38.001 --> 11:39.176
IF ALL IT TOOK TO SAVE
HER PEOPLE FROM THAT

11:39.220 --> 11:40.743
AND DELIVER THEM
TO THE PROMISED LAND

11:40.787 --> 11:43.746
WAS SURRENDER,
WOULD SHE DO IT?

11:43.790 --> 11:45.182
I WOULD HOPE SO.

11:45.226 --> 11:46.836
OF COURSE, YOU WOULD
NEVER SEE THE PROMISED LAND

11:46.880 --> 11:48.620
BECAUSE SHE WOULD KNOW
IT WAS YOU

11:48.664 --> 11:50.753
AND, BROTHER OR NOT,
THROW YOU IN THE PITS.

11:50.797 --> 11:53.930
NOT IF SHE THOUGHT
IT WAS COOPER.

11:53.974 --> 11:56.759
THERE'S A FAILSAFE IN
THE PROCESSING ROOM--

11:56.803 --> 11:58.152
I SAW IT
WHEN I WAS THERE--

11:58.195 --> 11:59.936
A WAY TO KILL THE WORMS
IF THEY EVER--

11:59.980 --> 12:02.460
FOLLY! COOPER WOULD
NEVER PUSH THAT BUTTON,

12:02.504 --> 12:04.898
AND SINCE SHE'S THE ONLY ONE
THAT HANDLES THE WORMS--

12:04.941 --> 12:07.291
COOPER
WOULD BE DEAD.

12:07.335 --> 12:10.860
WE'LL MAKE IT LOOK
LIKE AN ACCIDENT.

12:10.904 --> 12:13.384
YOU WOULD BE
THE FIRST RESPONDER.

12:13.428 --> 12:15.909
YOU WOULD HIT
THE FAILSAFE BUTTON.

12:15.952 --> 12:18.215
NO MORE WORMS.

12:23.046 --> 12:25.745
NO MORE WAR.

12:36.059 --> 12:37.887
OCTAVIA: WE KNOW THAT THERE ARE
3 ENTRY POINTS TO THE VALLEY.

12:37.931 --> 12:39.628
WHILE COOPER, MADI, AND I
SOFTEN THE BATTLEFIELD,

12:39.671 --> 12:40.847
MILLER WILL LEAD
THE FIRST BATTALION

12:40.890 --> 12:42.805
THROUGH THE SOUTHERN
TRIBUTARY.

12:42.849 --> 12:45.677
-FIRST?
-YOU HAVE A PROBLEM WITH THAT?

12:45.721 --> 12:48.289
NO, BUT THE FIRST
BATTALION'S INDRA'S.

12:48.332 --> 12:49.812
NOT ANYMORE.

12:49.856 --> 12:51.901
INDRA: IT'S FINE, NATHAN.
YOU'RE PREPARED.

12:51.945 --> 12:57.080
OCTAVIA: ALL RIGHT.
MADI, COME HERE BY ME.

12:58.603 --> 13:00.736
COOPER,
THE FLOOR IS YOURS.

13:00.780 --> 13:02.564
WORMS ARE THERMORECEPTORS.

13:02.607 --> 13:04.522
THAT MEANS
THEY SENSE BODY HEAT.

13:04.566 --> 13:06.002
WITH MADI'S KNOWLEDGE
OF THE WOODS,

13:06.046 --> 13:08.004
WE'LL GET AS CLOSE
TO THE VILLAGE AS WE CAN

13:08.048 --> 13:11.225
AND RELEASE THEM HERE, HERE,

13:11.268 --> 13:14.358
AND HERE.

13:14.402 --> 13:16.970
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

13:23.628 --> 13:27.110
VINSON: WHICH ONE
OF YOU IS RAVEN REYES?

13:32.637 --> 13:34.030
WHY IS HE WEARING
A COLLAR?

13:34.074 --> 13:37.294
-YOU DON'T WANT TO KNOW.
-TELL ME.

13:37.338 --> 13:38.774
SHAW: SERIAL KILLER.

13:38.818 --> 13:40.820
HE KEPT HIS VICTIMS'
HANDS AND FEET AS MEMENTOS.

13:40.863 --> 13:43.387
OTHER THAN THAT,
HE'S A NICE GUY.

13:43.431 --> 13:45.476
HMM.

13:45.520 --> 13:48.392
SHAW: WHAT'S THIS
ABOUT, VINSON?

13:48.436 --> 13:50.917
COLLAR LOOKS GOOD
ON YOU, SHAW.

13:50.960 --> 13:54.398
YOURS HAS BEEN TAGGED TO
ANOTHER FACILITY FOR THE DAY.

13:54.442 --> 13:58.315
NOW WALK WITH ME.

14:01.362 --> 14:04.974
I'LL BE OK.

14:13.461 --> 14:15.071
[DOOR OPENS]

14:19.467 --> 14:22.296
-GOOD.
-HEY, MAN.

14:28.780 --> 14:32.306
RAVEN: ABBY. OH...

14:34.482 --> 14:36.266
THANK YOU, VINSON.

14:43.795 --> 14:46.407
I'VE BEEN HERE
FOR DAYS.

14:46.450 --> 14:49.932
YOU'RE NOT COLLARED.

14:49.976 --> 14:54.502
I SAW KANE.
WHY HAVEN'T I SEEN YOU?

14:54.545 --> 14:56.983
I'M SORRY.

14:57.026 --> 15:00.900
ECHO SAID YOU DEFECTED
BECAUSE OF OCTAVIA.

15:03.163 --> 15:07.254
DID THEY TELL YOU
WHY YOU ARE HERE?

15:07.297 --> 15:08.733
NO.

15:08.777 --> 15:10.997
THE MINERS ARE SICK.

15:11.040 --> 15:13.129
I KNOW.
THE HYTHYLODIUM.

15:13.173 --> 15:14.957
LISTEN. I THINK
I CAN CURE THEM.

15:15.001 --> 15:17.960
I NEED YOU TO BE ABLE TO
TAKE THE POWER FROM THIS

15:18.004 --> 15:21.137
AND MAKE IT COME
OUT OF THIS.

15:21.181 --> 15:25.968
NO. IF THEY'RE
DYING, LET THEM.

15:26.012 --> 15:30.146
RAVEN, I'M A DOCTOR.
I CANNOT DO THAT.

15:30.190 --> 15:32.757
NOW PLEASE JUST TELL ME IF
IT'S EVEN AT ALL POSSIBLE.

15:32.801 --> 15:35.760
SURE. IT'S POSSIBLE,
BUT I'M NOT DOING IT.

15:35.804 --> 15:38.502
RAVEN, PLEASE.

15:38.546 --> 15:41.723
I NEED THIS TO WORK.

15:41.766 --> 15:44.291
ABBY, WHAT AREN'T
YOU TELLING ME?

15:46.554 --> 15:50.427
DID DIYOZA THREATEN
TO HURT YOU?

15:59.349 --> 16:00.437
I DON'T LIKE IT,

16:00.481 --> 16:05.051
BUT I'LL SEE
WHAT I CAN DO.

16:18.238 --> 16:22.459
I ADMIT IT.
I'M IMPRESSED.

16:24.984 --> 16:28.378
YOUR MOTHER WOULD
BE PROUD, MONTY.

16:28.422 --> 16:29.771
I TOLD YOU.

16:29.814 --> 16:31.251
IT'S THE NITROGEN,

16:31.294 --> 16:32.774
AND THAT TOOK
LESS THAN A DAY.

16:32.817 --> 16:37.170
IN A WEEK, THE ENTIRE
FARM COULD BE--

16:37.213 --> 16:39.259
YOU DON'T WANT
TO DO THAT.

16:39.302 --> 16:41.478
THE FIRST CULTURE,
EVEN FROM AN OLD STRAIN

16:41.522 --> 16:43.567
LIKE THIS, ISN'T SAFE.

16:43.611 --> 16:45.047
I MEAN, IT IS
FOR THE PLANTS,

16:45.091 --> 16:46.570
BUT ON THE RING,
IT PUT ONE

16:46.614 --> 16:48.616
OF MY FRIENDS
IN A COMA.

16:48.659 --> 16:51.097
I'LL KEEP THAT
IN MIND.

16:53.273 --> 16:57.277
MONTY, HERE'S THE TRUTH.
WE LEAVE IN A FEW HOURS.

16:57.320 --> 16:59.975
AFTER THAT, I DON'T EVER WANT
TO SEE THIS PLACE AGAIN.

17:00.019 --> 17:02.586
IF YOU WANT
TO TAKE IT OVER,

17:02.630 --> 17:05.154
BE MY GUEST.

17:05.198 --> 17:06.721
IF YOU'LL
EXCUSE ME...

17:06.764 --> 17:08.984
YOU DON'T
HAVE TO LEAVE.

17:09.028 --> 17:12.248
LOOK. THAT'S THE POINT.
NO ONE ELSE HAS TO DIE.

17:12.292 --> 17:15.991
YOU DID THINGS TO SURVIVE.
THAT'S IN THE PAST.

17:16.035 --> 17:19.603
WE CAN HAVE PROTEIN
AND BIOFUEL AND BEER.

17:19.647 --> 17:21.214
YEAH.
IT TASTES LIKE CRAP,

17:21.257 --> 17:23.912
BUT WHO CARES IF IT
GETS YOU DRUNK?

17:23.955 --> 17:26.436
[CHUCKLES]

17:31.659 --> 17:34.488
IS SOMEONE THERE?

17:34.531 --> 17:37.621
MM! UH!

17:37.665 --> 17:38.753
BELLAMY!

17:38.796 --> 17:41.016
[GLASS SHATTERS]

17:45.586 --> 17:46.935
CLARKE: MONTY, COME ON.

17:46.978 --> 17:48.110
WE NEED YOU TO OPEN
THE PROCESSING ROOM.

17:48.154 --> 17:49.633
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING?

17:49.677 --> 17:51.113
BELLAMY:
EXPLAIN LATER.

17:51.157 --> 17:52.549
ACTUALLY, IF YOU WANT
ME TO OPEN THAT DOOR,

17:52.593 --> 17:53.811
YOU'LL EXPLAIN NOW.

17:53.855 --> 17:55.944
I KNOW IT DOESN'T
LOOK LIKE IT,

17:55.987 --> 17:57.641
BUT THIS IS HOW
WE STOP THE WAR.

17:57.685 --> 17:59.034
I WAS STOPPING
THE WAR.

17:59.078 --> 18:01.254
KEEP YOUR VOICE DOWN.
IF ANYONE HEARS US--

18:01.297 --> 18:03.647
YOU'RE KILLING HER,
AREN'T YOU?

18:03.691 --> 18:06.172
YES.

18:06.215 --> 18:09.000
BELLAMY: IF YOU DON'T
OPEN THAT DOOR,

18:09.044 --> 18:14.658
WE'RE THE ONES
WHO GET KILLED.

18:14.702 --> 18:17.139
CLARKE: OPEN IT, MONTY.

18:17.183 --> 18:19.576
AND, OF COURSE,
I HELP

18:19.620 --> 18:22.188
BECAUSE WHAT'S
ONE MORE, RIGHT?

18:22.231 --> 18:25.060
-WE'RE ALREADY MURDERS.
-THAT'S NOT FAIR.

18:25.104 --> 18:27.323
WE'RE TALKING ABOUT TAKING
ONE LIFE TO SAVE HUNDREDS.

18:27.367 --> 18:31.197
MONTY: REALLY?
THEN LET'S KILL OCTAVIA.

18:33.938 --> 18:36.898
DIDN'T THINK SO.

18:37.986 --> 18:40.467
[CLANK]

18:45.385 --> 18:47.561
MONTY...

18:48.866 --> 18:50.607
[CLANK]

18:52.131 --> 18:54.698
WE'RE DOING
THE RIGHT THING.

18:54.742 --> 18:57.223
IF YOU SAY IT ENOUGH,

18:57.266 --> 19:00.226
MAYBE I'LL
BELIEVE YOU.

19:14.544 --> 19:17.504
[MCCREARY MOANING]

19:32.780 --> 19:36.218
[CHAINS RATTLE]

19:39.178 --> 19:40.875
LOOKS LIKE I SHOULD
HAVE KILLED YOU

19:40.918 --> 19:42.659
WHEN I HAD THE CHANCE.

19:42.703 --> 19:45.488
YEAH? WELL,
I'M HARD TO KILL.

19:47.882 --> 19:49.753
EMORI, HE'S UP.

19:49.797 --> 19:52.408
[COUGHING]

19:52.452 --> 19:55.237
GETTING BLOWN UP
MUST SUCK, HUH?

19:55.281 --> 19:57.892
NO. CHRONIC LUNG
DISEASE IS WORSE.

19:57.935 --> 20:00.329
I'LL TAKE
YOUR WORD FOR IT.

20:00.373 --> 20:02.157
EMORI!

20:02.201 --> 20:04.768
THE BOMB WAS
CLEVER, THOUGH.

20:04.812 --> 20:08.772
YEAH. IT WAS.
ROCKET FUEL.

20:08.816 --> 20:10.948
YOU SHOULD SEE WHAT
HYTHYLODIUM DOES

20:10.992 --> 20:13.429
WHEN IT'S
WEAPONIZED.

20:13.473 --> 20:16.693
I COULD USE SOMEONE
LIKE YOU ON MY CREW.

20:16.737 --> 20:17.955
NOW, SEE, THAT'S
FUNNY TO ME

20:17.999 --> 20:19.957
BECAUSE YOUR CREW
DOESN'T SEEM

20:20.001 --> 20:21.350
TO MISS YOU
MUCH AT ALL.

20:21.394 --> 20:23.352
WE OFFERED TO TRADE
YOU FOR RAVEN,

20:23.396 --> 20:26.442
YET HERE YOU
STILL ARE.

20:28.836 --> 20:30.533
DIYOZA SAID NO.

20:30.577 --> 20:32.579
WELL, ACTUALLY, I
BELIEVE HER EXACT WORDS

20:32.622 --> 20:36.583
WERE, "MAY GOD HAVE
MERCY ON HIS SOUL."

20:40.848 --> 20:44.634
I CAN HELP YOU

20:44.678 --> 20:48.421
GET RAVEN BACK.

20:50.945 --> 20:54.383
I'M LISTENING.

20:56.864 --> 21:00.302
[FOOTSTEPS]

21:06.221 --> 21:09.355
DIYOZA: THANKS, CASH.
WAIT HERE.

21:13.663 --> 21:16.405
[EXHALES]

21:16.449 --> 21:21.018
I'VE BEEN FIGHTING
THE ABUSE OF POWER

21:21.062 --> 21:22.759
MY WHOLE LIFE, KANE.

21:22.803 --> 21:24.108
I'M NO DICTATOR.

21:24.152 --> 21:25.545
[CHUCKLES]

21:25.588 --> 21:26.850
I WANT TO SEE AN END
TO THE VIOLENCE

21:26.894 --> 21:28.461
JUST AS BADLY AS YOU.

21:28.504 --> 21:29.897
YET THOSE WEREN'T EXACTLY
CIVIL ENGINEERING PLANS

21:29.940 --> 21:31.464
I SAW IN YOUR
NOTEBOOK, WERE THEY?

21:31.507 --> 21:33.553
PAGE AFTER PAGE
OF BATTLE STRATEGIES.

21:33.596 --> 21:38.384
DEFENSE STRATEGIES.
I'M NOT PREPARING FOR WAR.

21:38.427 --> 21:40.908
I'M PLANNING FOR PEACE.
THERE'S A DIFFERENCE.

21:40.951 --> 21:44.520
MAYBE SO, BUT UNTIL
YOU RECOGNIZE

21:44.564 --> 21:47.306
THAT WE'RE ALL
JUST PEOPLE,

21:47.349 --> 21:51.397
ALL THIS WILL EVER BE
IS A BATTLEFIELD.

21:52.746 --> 21:54.008
[EXHALES]

21:54.051 --> 21:57.490
KANE, WAIT.

21:59.143 --> 22:00.449
TELL ME WHAT
WE'RE LOOKING AT.

22:00.493 --> 22:03.234
I DON'T THINK WE'D
SEE IT THE SAME WAY,

22:03.278 --> 22:04.453
BUT ALL RIGHT.

22:04.497 --> 22:06.455
THAT'S WHERE THE
TRADING POST'LL BE,

22:06.499 --> 22:09.719
AND NEXT TO IT,
THERE'LL BE A FARM

22:09.763 --> 22:12.287
AND A WORKSHOP

22:12.331 --> 22:16.291
AND A MILL...

22:16.335 --> 22:20.339
AND A REAL MEDICAL
CENTER FOR ABBY.

22:22.210 --> 22:24.430
TO THE SOUTH,
THERE'LL BE HOMES

22:24.473 --> 22:27.389
DUG OUT OF THE GROUND
TO PRESERVE THE TREES,

22:27.433 --> 22:30.044
AND AT THE CENTER,
THERE'LL BE A WELL,

22:30.087 --> 22:34.135
PLACE FOR PEOPLE
TO GATHER, TALK,

22:34.178 --> 22:36.355
DEBATE IDEAS.

22:36.398 --> 22:39.923
AND A SCHOOL
WITH A PLAYGROUND

22:39.967 --> 22:41.534
WHERE KIDS CAN
BLOW OFF STEAM

22:41.577 --> 22:44.014
AND BITCH
ABOUT THEIR TEACHERS

22:44.058 --> 22:47.409
AND KISS
UNDER THE BLEACHERS.

22:50.978 --> 22:52.371
MY KID.

23:03.643 --> 23:05.427
HOW FAR ALONG?

23:05.471 --> 23:07.951
A HUNDRED YEARS
AND 5 MONTHS,

23:07.995 --> 23:09.866
GIVE OR TAKE.

23:09.910 --> 23:11.955
ABBY SAYS
SHE'S HEALTHY.

23:11.999 --> 23:14.610
A GIRL?

23:20.050 --> 23:23.793
WAS THAT A KICK?

23:23.837 --> 23:25.926
THANK YOU, KANE.

23:25.969 --> 23:27.362
FOR WHAT?

23:27.406 --> 23:29.973
UNTIL I MET YOU, THE THOUGHT
OF RAISING A CHILD

23:30.017 --> 23:34.717
IN A WORLD LIKE THIS--

23:37.851 --> 23:41.637
YOU GIVE ME HOPE.

23:41.681 --> 23:43.204
HOPE.

23:43.247 --> 23:45.902
[CHUCKLES]

23:45.946 --> 23:48.905
THAT'S A GOOD NAME.

23:48.949 --> 23:52.648
IT IS, ISN'T IT?

23:52.692 --> 23:55.216
HOPE.

24:10.187 --> 24:11.928
[PANTING]

24:18.718 --> 24:20.589
WHAT?

24:26.073 --> 24:29.511
OH, NO. NO. NO. NO.

24:31.078 --> 24:34.298
YOU'LL BOTH DIE FOR THIS.

24:34.342 --> 24:37.345
OH! NNGH!

24:37.388 --> 24:40.783
UH! NO! UH UH!

24:40.827 --> 24:45.745
RRGH! AAH!

24:45.788 --> 24:48.704
[MOANING]

24:51.098 --> 24:55.058
PLEASE MAKE IT STOP. AAH!

24:55.102 --> 24:57.626
[MOANING]

24:58.714 --> 25:00.237
AAH!

25:00.281 --> 25:02.588
LET'S GO.
IT'LL WORK.

25:02.631 --> 25:05.286
OCTAVIA WILL
HAVE TO SURRENDER.

25:05.329 --> 25:06.548
COOPER: PLEASE MAKE IT STOP!

25:06.592 --> 25:09.072
THIS IS HOW
WE GET TO PEACE.

25:09.116 --> 25:12.772
COOPER: AAGH! WHY?

25:12.815 --> 25:16.515
AAH!

25:39.102 --> 25:40.713
DROP THE GUN.

25:40.756 --> 25:42.976
-I SAID, DROP YOUR WEAPON.
-OH, OH, HEY, EASY, EASY, EASY.

25:43.019 --> 25:44.412
IT'S NOT LOADED.

25:44.455 --> 25:46.806
MCCREARY: WHY DON'T
YOU TAKE A MINUTE

25:46.849 --> 25:50.331
TO EXPLAIN
OUR ARRANGEMENT?

25:51.854 --> 25:55.728
EMORI.

25:55.771 --> 25:58.557
TELL ME YOU DIDN'T
MAKE A DEAL WITH THE MAN

25:58.600 --> 26:01.472
WHO TORTURED YOU AND
HUNTED YOU LIKE AN ANIMAL.

26:01.516 --> 26:03.126
-I DID.
-JOHN!

26:03.170 --> 26:05.085
THIS IS HOW
WE SAVE RAVEN.

26:05.128 --> 26:06.521
HOW?

26:06.565 --> 26:08.218
WALK RIGHT IN THE FRONT
DOOR AS HIS PRISONERS.

26:08.262 --> 26:09.306
THEY'LL COLLAR US
TO MAKE IT LOOK REAL,

26:09.350 --> 26:11.700
BUT I FIGURE--

26:11.744 --> 26:14.224
I KNOW HOW
TO TAKE THEM OFF.

26:14.268 --> 26:16.183
MM-HMM.

26:16.226 --> 26:18.577
HMM, I DON'T KNOW.

26:18.620 --> 26:20.622
-WE KILLED TWO OF HIS PEOPLE.
-LOOK, EMORI.

26:20.666 --> 26:22.145
I DON'T TRUST
THE GUY, EITHER,

26:22.189 --> 26:23.407
BUT WE WANT
THE SAME THING.

26:23.451 --> 26:26.672
-WHAT?
-TO SURVIVE. COME ON.

26:26.715 --> 26:29.631
WE ZIP IN, WE GET RAVEN,
WE ZIP OUT.

26:29.675 --> 26:33.069
WE GET THE OTHERS
AFTER, OK?

26:33.113 --> 26:36.290
OK. I'M IN.

26:36.333 --> 26:38.814
GOOD.

26:40.294 --> 26:43.558
THAT'S ALL
I'M IN FOR, JOHN.

26:44.907 --> 26:47.431
MURPHY: LOOK. I HATE TO
DO THIS WITH A PSYCHOPATH

26:47.475 --> 26:48.694
SITTING ON THE NEXT TREE,
BUT I THOUGHT THIS

26:48.737 --> 26:50.347
IS WHAT YOU WANTED,
YOU AND ME TOGETHER

26:50.391 --> 26:51.740
-YES. IT IS.
-WORKING AS A TEAM.

26:51.784 --> 26:53.612
JOHN, SEEING YOU
LIKE THIS,

26:53.655 --> 26:55.614
SEEING YOU FIGHTING
TO SURVIVE,

26:55.657 --> 26:58.834
THIS IS THE JOHN MURPHY
I FELL IN LOVE WITH.

26:58.878 --> 27:01.663
WE'RE RUNNING THROUGH
THE WOODS WITH A KILLER

27:01.707 --> 27:03.404
ABOUT TO BECOME
PRISONERS IN ORDER

27:03.447 --> 27:05.754
TO SAVE OUR FRIENDS,
AND I FIND MYSELF

27:05.798 --> 27:09.192
WANTING TO RIP
YOUR CLOTHES OFF.

27:09.236 --> 27:11.804
THIS--

27:11.847 --> 27:13.893
AS SOON AS THIS
FIGHT IS OVER,

27:13.936 --> 27:17.636
YOU WILL FALL
APART AGAIN.

27:17.679 --> 27:23.163
-EMORI--
-NO.

27:23.206 --> 27:26.035
TROUBLE IN PARADISE?

27:30.083 --> 27:33.173
NO. WE'RE GOOD HERE.

27:33.216 --> 27:35.610
TIE HER UP.

27:49.929 --> 27:54.194
ALL RIGHT, ABBY.
FIRE IT UP.

27:54.237 --> 27:56.152
ABBY?

28:01.027 --> 28:05.031
COME ON, SLEEPING BEAUTY.
YOU GOT TO SEE THIS.

28:05.074 --> 28:07.250
ABBY.

28:07.294 --> 28:10.863
ABBY. ABBY.

28:29.011 --> 28:34.495
WHAT THE HELL, ABBY?
WHAT ARE YOU TAKING?

28:34.538 --> 28:36.236
OHH...

28:36.279 --> 28:39.935
RAVEN, I CAN EXPLAIN.

28:39.979 --> 28:42.851
DO YOU REMEMBER THE PAIN
AFTER THE CITY OF LIGHT?

28:42.895 --> 28:47.551
DON'T YOU TALK
TO ME ABOUT PAIN.

28:47.595 --> 28:50.293
HOW DOES THIS WORK,
YOU HELP DIYOZA,

28:50.337 --> 28:52.731
AND SHE
GIVES YOU THESE?

28:52.774 --> 28:56.778
YOU WEREN'T SCARED
SHE WAS GONNA HURT YOU.

28:56.822 --> 29:00.303
YOU WERE SCARED SHE
WAS GONNA CUT YOU OFF.

29:00.347 --> 29:01.870
RAVEN, I WILL STOP.

29:01.914 --> 29:04.960
SAID BY EVERY ADDICT EVER!
WELL, SCREW THAT.

29:05.004 --> 29:08.877
I WILL NOT HELP YOU
GET YOUR NEXT FIX.

29:09.922 --> 29:12.315
I DIDN'T BUILD THIS
FOR A JUNKIE.

29:12.359 --> 29:13.316
[ZAP]

29:13.360 --> 29:15.318
AAGH!

29:15.362 --> 29:19.192
UH! AAH!

29:19.235 --> 29:20.541
SORRY, RAVEN.

29:20.584 --> 29:22.412
AAH! D'AAGH!

29:22.456 --> 29:26.155
I AM SO, SO SORRY.

29:34.773 --> 29:37.776
THERE YOU ARE.

29:40.256 --> 29:42.955
YOU OK?

29:42.998 --> 29:47.350
WE WERE HAPPY ONCE,
WEREN'T WE?

29:47.394 --> 29:49.222
YEAH.

29:59.928 --> 30:04.063
WE'LL GET BACK THERE,
I PROMISE.

30:05.978 --> 30:09.851
I DON'T WANT TO BE
A KILLER ANYMORE.

30:09.895 --> 30:13.028
I DON'T WANT TO TAKE
LIVES TO SAVE THEM.

30:14.334 --> 30:16.292
THEN DON'T.

30:16.336 --> 30:18.860
WHAT IF I SAY NO

30:18.904 --> 30:21.471
AND PEOPLE WE
CARE ABOUT DIE?

30:21.515 --> 30:22.864
THEY MIGHT,

30:22.908 --> 30:26.346
BUT EVERYONE
DIES, MONTY.

30:26.389 --> 30:28.565
[EXHALES]

30:28.609 --> 30:30.872
LET'S SHOW THEM
HOW TO LIVE.

30:33.832 --> 30:38.010
WILL YOU STILL LOVE ME
IF I'M JUST A FARMER?

30:43.929 --> 30:47.933
WHEN THE ARMY MARCHES,
WE STAY HERE.

30:58.465 --> 31:02.164
[ALARM BLARING]

31:16.091 --> 31:20.922
INDRA: I HEARD SCREAMS,
BUT I WAS TOO LATE.

31:25.144 --> 31:27.973
MILLER: THERE'S
A HOLE IN HER GLOVE.

31:28.016 --> 31:30.279
MUST HAVE GOT IN WHILE
SHE WAS LOADING THEM UP.

31:30.323 --> 31:31.759
I'M SORRY, BLODREINA.

31:31.802 --> 31:33.761
IF I DIDN'T USE THE GAS
AND THE WORMS ESCAPED

31:33.804 --> 31:37.678
-INTO THE BUNKER--
-YOU MADE THE RIGHT CALL, INDRA.

31:37.721 --> 31:40.942
OCTAVIA, I KNOW
THIS ISN'T A GOOD TIME,

31:40.986 --> 31:43.902
BUT I FEEL IT'S
MY DUTY TO POINT OUT

31:43.945 --> 31:46.078
THAT WITHOUT THE WORMS
TO SOFTEN THE BATTLEFIELD,

31:46.121 --> 31:48.863
THE COST IN LIVES
WILL BE TOO HIGH.

31:48.907 --> 31:50.560
THIS IS NOT A WAR
WE SHOULD FIGHT.

31:50.604 --> 31:54.347
HMM, THANK YOU FOR
YOUR ADVICE, SEDA,

31:54.390 --> 31:58.742
BUT WE WEREN'T PLANNING
ON USING THE WORMS.

31:58.786 --> 32:01.354
WE ARE USING
THEIR EGGS.

32:02.659 --> 32:04.139
WHOEVER WANTED
TO MAKE THIS LOOK

32:04.183 --> 32:08.013
LIKE AN ACCIDENT, THEY
DIDN'T KNOW THAT, EITHER.

32:11.059 --> 32:14.323
FIND CLARKE AND BELLAMY.

32:25.073 --> 32:28.163
YOU'RE A GOOD
BROTHER, BELLAMY.

32:28.207 --> 32:32.211
I'M SORRY THAT
I THOUGHT I COULD--

32:32.254 --> 32:34.126
KILL MY SISTER?

32:38.608 --> 32:42.612
THE TRUTH IS, IF SHE
WAS ANYBODY ELSE,

32:42.656 --> 32:44.701
I WOULD'VE
BEAT YOU TO IT.

32:44.745 --> 32:47.748
I DON'T KNOW
ABOUT THAT.

32:47.791 --> 32:52.144
MAYBE THE OLD BELLAMY,
BUT NOT THIS ONE.

32:52.187 --> 32:56.278
SUDDENLY, I'M THE ONE
LETTING MY HEART RULE MY HEAD.

32:58.498 --> 33:00.195
MAMA BEARS DON'T THINK.

33:00.239 --> 33:02.371
THEY JUST PROTECT
THEIR YOUNG.

33:03.894 --> 33:06.158
MILLER: UH!

33:06.201 --> 33:08.029
WHOA.

33:08.073 --> 33:10.118
-OCTAVIA--
-TAKE HER.

33:10.162 --> 33:12.860
MILLER: YOU'RE UNDER ARREST
FOR THE MURDER OF KARA COOPER.

33:12.903 --> 33:14.775
BELLAMY: WHAT? NO.
THIS IS INSANE.

33:14.818 --> 33:18.083
OCTAVIA: IS IT?
WE WEREN'T TAKING THE WORMS.

33:18.126 --> 33:20.259
THE EGGS ARE ALREADY
LOADED IN THE ROVER,

33:20.302 --> 33:24.437
SO WHAT WAS COOPER
DOING THERE?

33:26.613 --> 33:28.136
CAREFUL, BIG BROTHER,

33:28.180 --> 33:29.920
OR I'LL THINK YOU HELPED HER,
AND WE DON'T HAVE

33:29.964 --> 33:32.097
ENOUGH PRISONERS TO SETTLE THIS
IN THE ARENA.

33:34.273 --> 33:38.581
OH, WELL. I GUESS WE'LL HAVE
TO SETTLE FOR AN EXECUTION.

33:38.625 --> 33:40.583
-UH...
-LET'S GO.

33:40.627 --> 33:44.413
KEEP MADI SAFE.
PROMISE ME. UH!

33:44.457 --> 33:47.025
I PROMISE.

33:57.818 --> 34:00.038
MAN: WHAT HAPPENED
TO HER?

34:14.226 --> 34:18.056
YOU'LL BE HAPPY TO KNOW
I DIDN'T KILL YOUR PILOT.

34:24.584 --> 34:27.543
WE CAN'T LET
DIYOZA WIN.

34:27.587 --> 34:28.849
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

34:28.892 --> 34:32.287
PROMISE ME
HE WON'T SUFFER.

34:36.987 --> 34:41.775
SHAW: HEY,
DID HE HURT YOU?

34:41.818 --> 34:45.257
I'LL BE RIGHT OVER THERE
IF YOU NEED ME.

34:56.746 --> 34:59.793
-TELL ME THE TRUTH.
-WHY DO YOU CARE?

34:59.836 --> 35:01.664
YOU'RE THE REASON
THESE PEOPLE

35:01.708 --> 35:04.363
ARE STILL ALIVE,
RIGHT?

35:04.406 --> 35:07.322
THEIR SINS
ARE ON YOU NOW.

35:21.336 --> 35:24.774
HAVE YOU EVER LOVED
SOMEONE SO MUCH

35:24.818 --> 35:28.038
THAT, NO MATTER
WHAT THEY DO TO YOU

35:28.082 --> 35:34.523
OR THEMSELVES,
YOU TAKE IT?

35:37.047 --> 35:39.572
MOM OR DAD?

35:41.835 --> 35:43.924
MOM.

35:43.967 --> 35:47.101
DRANK HERSELF
TO DEATH.

35:51.932 --> 35:54.282
THE ANSWER IS YES.

35:57.807 --> 36:00.419
[SOBS]

36:02.769 --> 36:04.945
[SOBS]

36:05.772 --> 36:07.948
[SOBS]

36:09.776 --> 36:11.169
VINSON:
IS IT PERMANENT?

36:11.212 --> 36:13.258
THERE'S STILL SOME
RESIDUAL TISSUE DAMAGE.

36:13.301 --> 36:14.781
YOU WON'T BE RUNNING
ANY MARATHONS,

36:14.824 --> 36:16.870
BUT I CAN SAFELY SAY
THAT LUNG DISEASE

36:16.913 --> 36:18.828
IS NOT WHAT'S
GONNA KILL YOU.

36:18.872 --> 36:20.221
DIYOZA:
WELL DONE, ABBY.

36:20.265 --> 36:21.918
HOW SOON CAN YOU
DO THE OTHERS?

36:21.962 --> 36:24.399
MAN, ON RADIO: COLONEL,
WE GOT COMPANY,

36:24.443 --> 36:27.315
MOVEMENT
IN THE EAST WOODS.

36:27.359 --> 36:30.275
UH, SCRATCH THAT.
IT'S MCCREARY.

36:30.318 --> 36:33.408
LOOKS LIKE
HE'S GOT PRISONERS.

36:33.452 --> 36:36.237
EVERYTHING OK?

36:37.934 --> 36:40.981
YES...

36:43.375 --> 36:47.770
BUT IT'S A PITY YOU HAVEN'T
FOUND THE CURE YET.

36:47.814 --> 36:50.338
VINSON: RUTHLESS.
I LIKE IT.

36:50.382 --> 36:52.253
YOU WANT YOUR PILLS,
YOU'LL KEEP IT

36:52.297 --> 36:54.777
TO YOURSELF FOR NOW.

36:54.821 --> 36:57.563
DO WE UNDERSTAND
EACH OTHER?

37:01.480 --> 37:04.787
[RATTLE]

37:04.831 --> 37:07.486
[DOOR OPENS]

37:08.878 --> 37:10.271
[DOOR CLOSES]

37:10.315 --> 37:12.665
THANK YOU FOR
SAVING MY LIFE.

37:21.761 --> 37:24.677
HEY, HEY,
IT'S MCCREARY.

37:24.720 --> 37:27.593
[MEN CHEERING]

38:01.191 --> 38:03.759
OMON GON OSON.

38:05.892 --> 38:07.894
OMON GON OSON.

38:07.937 --> 38:09.852
MILLER: WHAT ABOUT
THE GIRL--MADI?

38:09.896 --> 38:13.247
OCTAVIA: SHE COMES WITH US
IN THE ROVER AS PLANNED.

38:13.291 --> 38:14.814
OMON GON OSON.

38:14.857 --> 38:18.165
OCTAVIA: ONCE SHE FINDS OUT
ABOUT IT, THE WAR WILL BE OVER,

38:18.208 --> 38:19.862
AND WE'LL DEAL WITH IT THEN.

38:19.906 --> 38:23.039
SORRY, BLODREINA.

38:23.083 --> 38:26.434
OCTAVIA: LET HIM IN.

38:26.478 --> 38:30.786
GET SOME SLEEP.
TOMORROW WE RIDE.

38:32.222 --> 38:34.964
SO MUCH FOR THE 100.

38:35.008 --> 38:38.446
-WHAT?
-LET IT GO, MILLER.

38:44.931 --> 38:46.846
[DOOR CLOSES]

38:46.889 --> 38:49.631
DON'T THREATEN
MY PEOPLE, BELLAMY.

38:51.459 --> 38:54.723
I CAN'T LET YOU
KILL CLARKE, O.

38:54.767 --> 38:56.377
HERE WE GO AGAIN,

38:56.421 --> 38:59.902
PLEADING FOR
THE LIFE OF A TRAITOR

38:59.946 --> 39:01.730
WHO YOU LOVE.

39:08.607 --> 39:11.827
MOM AND I USED TO SHARE
OUR RATIONS WITH YOU.

39:11.871 --> 39:13.916
YOU MIND?

39:13.960 --> 39:16.441
ONLY IF YOU
SAY THE WORDS.

39:18.660 --> 39:22.360
THROUGH THE TEETH
AND OVER THE GUMS...

39:22.403 --> 39:25.537
NOT THOSE WORDS.

39:27.974 --> 39:32.935
OMON GON OSON.
SAY IT.

39:32.979 --> 39:36.286
OMON GON OSON.

39:45.731 --> 39:48.386
OMON GON OSON.

39:54.348 --> 39:56.045
IT'S LATE, BELLAMY.

39:56.089 --> 40:00.223
IF YOU'VE COME HERE
TO BEG, JUST DO IT.

40:00.267 --> 40:02.095
I'M NOT HERE TO BEG.

40:02.138 --> 40:06.491
I CAME HERE TO TELL YOU
THAT I LOVE YOU

40:06.534 --> 40:12.105
VERY MUCH, NO MATTER
WHAT HAPPENS.

40:12.148 --> 40:15.413
I HOPE YOU BELIEVE ME.

40:17.197 --> 40:20.330
GET TO THE POINT.

40:22.028 --> 40:23.986
I MADE A DEAL
WITH DIYOZA.

40:24.030 --> 40:26.293
IF WONKRU SURRENDERS,

40:26.336 --> 40:29.427
WE CAN ALL LIVE
IN THE VALLEY.

40:32.517 --> 40:34.562
HOW--

40:34.606 --> 40:37.130
[GASPING]

40:37.173 --> 40:40.307
SOMETHING'S WRONG.

40:40.350 --> 40:43.919
I--I CAN'T BREATHE.

40:43.963 --> 40:47.009
HELP ME. HELP ME.

40:47.053 --> 40:50.448
[GASPING]

40:50.491 --> 40:53.973
WHAT DID YOU DO?

40:54.016 --> 40:57.237
I DOSED THE BAR

40:57.280 --> 41:00.458
WITH MONTY'S ALGAE.

41:00.501 --> 41:03.025
I SWITCHED IT WITH
THE ONE WE WERE SHARING.

41:03.069 --> 41:05.332
[GASPS]

41:05.375 --> 41:07.160
-GUARD!
-HEY...

41:07.203 --> 41:11.773
[MUFFLED SHOUTING]

41:11.817 --> 41:14.036
HEY...

41:14.080 --> 41:16.474
[SHOUTING STOPS]

41:21.000 --> 41:25.352
SHH. YOU'LL BE OK.

41:25.395 --> 41:31.053
BY THE TIME YOU WAKE UP,
WE'LL BE IN THE VALLEY.

41:31.097 --> 41:33.882
WE WILL HAVE PEACE.

41:35.928 --> 41:38.670
[GASPS]

41:43.370 --> 41:47.069
MY SISTER,

41:47.113 --> 41:49.855
MY RESPONSIBILITY.
